2026-06-08 | Partition Array According to Given Pivot

	Question
Return the rearranged array.
	Key Insight
This is a stable partition problem.
Create three separate groups:
		less than pivot
		equal to pivot
		greater than pivot
Then concatenate them.
This automatically preserves the original order.
	Approach
1.	Create three vectors:
		less
		equal
		greater
2.	Traverse nums:
		if num < pivot
				push into less
		else if num == pivot
				push into equal
		else
				push into greater
3.	Append:
		less + equal + greater
4.	Return result.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> pivotArray(vector<int>& nums, int pivot) {
        vector<int> less;
        vector<int> equal;
        vector<int> greater;
        for(int num : nums) {
            if(num < pivot)
                less.push_back(num);
            else if(num == pivot)
                equal.push_back(num);
            else
                greater.push_back(num);
        }
        vector<int> ans;
        ans.insert(ans.end(),
                   less.begin(),
                   less.end());
        ans.insert(ans.end(),
                   equal.begin(),
                   equal.end());
        ans.insert(ans.end(),
                   greater.begin(),
                   greater.end());
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
By separating elements into three stable groups:
		less than pivot
		equal to pivot
		greater than pivot
and then joining them together, we satisfy all ordering requirements in a single pass.
